Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Best Medical Billing And Coding Service For You Medical billing and coding are two critical components of the healthcare industry that ensure healthcare providers are compensated for the services they render. These two practices work hand-in-hand to facilitate the reimbursement process, translating medical procedures into numeric or alphanumeric codes and processing insurance claims for healthcare services. Medical Coding Medical coding is a fundamental aspect of healthcare that plays a vital role in the billing and reimbursement process. It involves the translation of medical procedures, diagnoses, and treatments into a standardized code format that can be easily understood by healthcare providers, insurance companies, and government agencies. The process of medical coding begins with a patient's visit to a healthcare provider. During this visit, the provider takes note of the patient's symptoms, performs various tests, and makes a diagnosis. The provider then prescribes a course of treatment, which may include medication, physical therapy, or surgery.

Description: Thomas Products LLC is a mid-sized animal food manufacturer in Madera, California.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: TPi was incorporated in May, 1989 and officially opened in 1990. Their stock was purchased by Land O' Lakes Purina Feed in July, 1997, and they operate as a wholly owned subsidiary. Their manufacturing plant is located in Madera, CA and their hub for distribution to customers located in the Pacific Northwest is in Hubbard, OR(which is just south of Portland). They also have a sales office in Twin Falls, ID catering to the needs of their customers in Idaho, Utah, Montana, and Nevada. TPi stocks over 1000 microingredients (vitamins, trace minerals, amino acids, neutraceuticals, etc…), manufactures custom premixes, and operates distribution channels to customers west of the Rockies. They also distribute internationally to several countries along the Pacific Rim, Canada, and Mexico. Their primary customers are livestock and companion animal feed companies and integrated livestock companies. They also work closely with independent nutritionists and other companies in their industry who require high quality and peace of mind that certain products make it to their customers. Everyday their goal is to treat customers how they would like to be treated while providing a level of quality assurance surpassing industry standards. While the majority of their business is livestock, primarily dairy cows, many of the microingredients they handle are resold to other species of animals. The spectrum of species ranges from lorikeets, to crickets, to bees, to sea bass, to exotic zoo animals. Each creature or specie of animal has unique nutritional requirements as well as particular physical characteristics. They have learned and cooperated with customers over the years in a manner that has grown to meet the unique demand for this niche market.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Food and Beverage, Manufacturing

Description: A creative agency to help your science have impact
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Most scientists struggle in their efforts to connect with a public audience. Because a public audience craves something we’re not trained to deliver as scientists: story. Story is the most important tool we have to engage human beings. Stories can educate, inspire, and drive action. But developing a powerful story is a skillset like any other. It takes time and training most scientists simply do not have. Here at Impact Media Lab, we work with scientists and science organizations to find the compelling threads in their research, then develop multimedia campaigns to share those stories with the world. Because we believe science is most impactful when we use the language of story. Over the past 5 years, our team has grown to include writers and filmmakers, photographers and illustrators, designers and journalists, all working together to tell meaningful stories about science. We have won awards, found adventure, and made lifelong friends in the greatest clients the world has ever known. If you’re a scientist or science organization looking to connect with a public audience, let’s dive into your story together!
